('16633', '427', 'Hydrocarbons', 'Raw fossil fuels such as petroleum and mineral oil. Hydrocarbons are crucial building blocks in the production of organic chemicals, plastics and waxes, and are thus one of the most useful materials harvestable from any source.', '50_09', '0', '0.1', '1', '1', '0', '2', '501'),
('16634', '427', 'Atmospheric Gases', 'Nitrogen, oxygen, neon, helium, xenon, methane, nitrous oxide, ozone -- a host of trapped vapours that can be used to catalyze numerous chemical processes.', '50_08', '0', '0.1', '1', '1', '0', '2', '501'),
('16635', '427', 'Evaporite Deposits', 'Deposits formed by the precipitation of mineral-rich water. Usable for many purposes, mostly as building-block components for more complex materials.\r\n', '50_07', '0', '0.1', '1', '1', '0', '2', '501'),
