('17977', '465', 'Smooth Glacial Mass', 'Interstellar ices are formed by accretion of gas molecules onto silicate dust particles. Glacial masses are known to contain hydrogen isotopes in abundance, but the high surface diffusion on this particular mass means it has considerably more than its coarser counterparts.\r\n', '51_04', '1000', '1000', '0', '1', '0', '116000', '493'),
('17978', '465', 'Enriched Clear Icicle', 'Interstellar ices are formed by accretion of gas molecules onto silicate dust particles. These crystalline formations can be found scattered around many an ice field and are known as the universe''s primary source of helium isotopes. Due to environmental factors, this fragment''s isotope deposits have become even richer than its regular counterparts''.', '51_02', '1000', '1000', '0', '1', '0', '466000', '493'),
